Hi, thanks for the feedback. I tried your solution and I genuinely don't know why it is giving an answer larger than what the expected result is. I translated my C++ Solution code into python (sorry if it's bad, I don't use python) and it passes all the tests. I do see that you have a different implementation but not exactly sure why it also doesn't work. 

import sys

n = int(input())
cs = [int(input()) for _ in range(n)]

for s in range(len(cs)):
    cs[s] *= cs[s]

cs.sort()

ans = cs[0] * 4

for c in range(len(cs)):
    if cs[c] != cs[0] and cs[c] != cs[-1]:
        ans += cs[c] * 5 - cs[c - 1]

if n > 1:
    ans += ((cs[n - 1] * 6) - cs[n - 2])
else:
    ans += cs[0]

print(ans)
